steps.apply:
{A}+ = {A}
Apply A -> BCEF: {A, B, C, E, F}
Apply E -> DG: {A, B, C, D, E, F, G}
All 7 attributes covered. So A is a superkey.
Is it minimal? A is a single attribute, so it is trivially minimal.
Conclusion: {A} is a candidate key.

{BC}+ = {B, C}
Apply BC -> A: {A, B, C}
Apply A -> BCEF: {A, B, C, E, F}
Apply E -> DG: {A, B, C, D, E, F, G}
All 7 attributes covered. So BC is a superkey.
Minimality: Check {B}+ = {B} (B alone cannot determine A or anything else from the given FDs). Check {C}+ = {C}. Neither B nor C alone is a superkey. So {BC} is minimal.
Conclusion: {BC} is a candidate key.
